The paper deals with real-time bidding strategies for group-buying ads, which involves optimization of bid values to maximize profits. This falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with the selection and ranking of ads based on user queries. The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it deals with the optimization of profits for both the advertiser and the bidder. The use of real-time bidding and optimization algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.MA, cs.LG).
